SIMPLE: exorcist
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exorcist
<hw>Ex"or*cist</hw> <pr>(-s⟦icr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exorcista</ets>, Gr. <grk>'exorkisth`s</grk>: cf. F.
<ets>exorciste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who expels evil
spirits by conjuration or exorcism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Certain of the vagabond Jews, <qex>exorcists</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Acts xix. 13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A conjurer who can raise spirits.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou, like an <qex>exorcist</qex>, hast conjured up⟦br⟧
My mortified spirit.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exordial</ent>⟦br⟧
